President Obama issued a statement on the 15th anniversary of the Good Friday Agreement, praising the progress made by the people and leaders of Northern Ireland. He acknowledged the steps taken to move away from violence and division towards dialogue and cooperation. The President also emphasized the need to continue working towards peace and prosperity, rejecting those who promote hate and looking backward. He expressed the United States' commitment to being a friend and partner to Northern Ireland, and pledged continued support for their efforts to build a strong society, vibrant economy, and lasting peace.